@maps @regression @staff
Feature: TC_11_STAFF - Parcel Search Format Tolerance

  # Migrated from legacy "Regression Pack for Map Printing Case Sensitive"
  # (BISSAGL-8080 AT-TC-01 to 05).
  #
  # BUSINESS FLOW
  #   Parcel numbers are entered by hand and arrive in inconsistent formats. The search must
  #   normalise case and tolerate stray characters, resolving to the same parcel either way.
  #
  # WHAT THIS VALIDATES
  #   Intended: lower case, upper case, trailing special characters, invalid values and a
  #   blank value all behave correctly on the parcel search.
  #
  # LEGACY DEFECT - THIS PACK NO LONGER TESTS WHAT IT IS NAMED FOR
  #   The commented-out literals show the original intent:
  #     AT-TC-01 "o1170800024"   lower case
  #     AT-TC-02 "O1170800024"   upper case
  #     AT-TC-03 "O1060300013*"  trailing special character
  #     AT-TC-04 "4354543648894" invalid
  #     AT-TC-05 " "             blank
  #   When the pack was moved to DB-driven data, those literals were replaced with parcel
  #   rows 11-15 - which are all valid, correctly-cased LPIS parcels. Sections 1-3 now search
  #   three valid parcels three times, and Section 5 searches a fourth. The case-insensitivity
  #   and blank-input coverage was lost silently in the refactor.
  #   Sections 1-3 and 5 below preserve the current (weakened) behaviour rather than invent
  #   new coverage. Section 4 keeps the invalid literals that ARE still live in legacy.
  #   ACTION: restore intent by deriving case variants from one DB parcel at runtime -
  #   e.g. "the next LPIS parcel in lower case" - which needs a step def, not new test data.

  @staffdata @parcels:15
  Background:
    Given the staff user is logged in to the BISS internal portal as "agr11612"
    And the staff user is on the Map Printing screen
    And the staff user is searching by parcel

  @e2e @validation
  Scenario: Staff searches parcels in varying formats and reaches the generation settings

    # SECTION 1 - AT-TC-01 (BISSAGL-14833) - intended: lower case
    When the staff user searches Map Printing for the next LPIS parcel for scheme year "2023"
    Then the generate map settings should be available

    # SECTION 2 - AT-TC-02 (BISSAGL-14832) - intended: upper case
    When the staff user searches Map Printing for the next LPIS parcel for scheme year "2023"
    Then the generate map settings should be available

    # SECTION 3 - AT-TC-03 (BISSAGL-14831) - intended: trailing special character
    When the staff user searches Map Printing for the next LPIS parcel for scheme year "2023"
    Then the generate map settings should be available

    # SECTION 4 - AT-TC-04 (BISSAGL-14824)
    # Validates: three malformed parcel values in sequence. Legacy asserts the settings
    # section is still available after each - i.e. the screen does not break on bad input.
    When the staff user searches Map Printing for the next LPIS parcel for scheme year "2023"
    Then the generate map settings should be available
    When the staff user searches Map Printing for each of the following invalid parcels for scheme year "2023"
      | hdgfhggdfhjkdhj |
      | 345dhf564gh48   |
    Then the generate map settings should be available

    # SECTION 5 - AT-TC-05 (BISSAGL-14823) - intended: blank value
    When the staff user searches Map Printing for the next LPIS parcel for scheme year "2023"
    Then the generate map settings should be available
