# ====================================================================================================================================
# TC_07_STAFF.feature
# ====================================================================================================================================
@sim @regression @staff
Feature: TC_07_STAFF - SIM Amendments and History Audit Trail

  # Migrated from legacy "Regression Suite for SIM Amendments - History Tab"
  # (BISSAGL-5444 AT-TC-01).
  #
  # BUSINESS FLOW
  #   Staff amend SIM parcel data on a submitted application - the area found on inspection,
  #   the area the farmer claimed, and whether the parcel carries SIM at all. Every such
  #   amendment is an auditable act on a live scheme application, so each one must leave a
  #   trace on the History tab. The pack then submits the SIM amendments and reverts the
  #   herd to its starting state so the fixture survives for the next run.
  #
  # WHAT THIS VALIDATES
  #   1. Amending SIM found area records history.
  #   2. Amending SIM claimed area records history.
  #   3. Toggling the SIM indicator on a parcel records history.
  #   4. Submitting SIM amendments records history.
  #   5. The herd can be reverted to its original SIM state.
  #
  # TEST DATA NOTE
  #   Legacy loaded "Get 1 Herds with Submission" but then OVERRODE it with hardcoded
  #   G175C038, leaving the DB step commented out. Kept as a literal: this pack needs a herd
  #   carrying the three specific SIM parcels below. A generic submitted herd would fail at
  #   the first parcel step.
  #   ACTION: a "herds with SIM parcels" DBRouter case would remove all four literals.

  Background:
    Given the staff user is logged in to the BISS internal portal as "agr4442"
    And the staff user has opened the SIM screen for herd "G175C038" for scheme year "2023"

  @e2e @history @audit
  Scenario: Staff amends SIM parcel data and each amendment is recorded in history

    # SECTION 1 - AT-TC-01 (BISSAGL-14998)
    # Validates: amending the area found on a SIM parcel is recorded as an auditable event.
    When the staff user amends SIM parcel "G17202130" with the following values
      | simFoundArea | 4 |
    Then the amendment should be recorded in the application history

    # SECTION 2
    # Validates: amending the claimed area is likewise audited - a different field on a
    # different parcel, proving the audit is not specific to one input.
    When the staff user amends SIM parcel "G22814025" with the following values
      | amendedClaimedArea | 6 |
    Then the amendment should be recorded in the application history

    # SECTION 3
    # Validates: toggling the SIM indicator - a scheme eligibility change rather than an
    # area correction - is audited in the same way.
    When the staff user toggles the SIM indicator on parcel "G22813057"
    Then the amendment should be recorded in the application history

    # SECTION 4
    # Validates: submitting the accumulated amendments is itself an audited event.
    When the staff user submits the SIM amendments with note "Test 7678"
    And the staff user toggles the SIM scheme option
    Then the amendment should be recorded in the application history

    # SECTION 5 - fixture reset
