@active-farmer @regression @staff
Feature: TC_16_STAFF - Active Farmer Admin Check and Appeal Lifecycle

  # Migrated from legacy "Regression Pack for Active Farmer History Notes - In Progress to be
  # cleared" (BISSAGL-7777 AT-TC-01 to 03).
  #
  # BUSINESS FLOW
  #   Where a farmer's active status is in doubt, staff start an admin check. Starting one
  #   applies a STOP to the application, which blocks payment until resolved. Approving the
  #   check lifts the stop; rejecting it leaves the stop in place, and the farmer may then
  #   appeal by submitting evidence, which staff review and can approve - lifting the stop.
  #   Every transition writes a system note to the History screen, because each one changes
  #   whether public money is paid out.
  #
  # WHAT THIS VALIDATES
  #   1. Starting an admin check applies the stop and writes the correct history note.
  #   2. Approving the check lifts the stop and writes the note carrying the staff comment.
  #   3. A rejected check can be appealed with evidence, and approving the appeal lifts the
  #      stop with the appeal comment recorded.
  #
  # SECTION ORDERING - IMPORTANT
  #   Legacy AT-TC-02 has its "Start admin check" steps commented out: it silently assumes
  #   the check started by AT-TC-01 is still in progress on the SAME herd. That implicit
  #   dependency between two "independent" scenarios is exactly the kind of thing that breaks
  #   when tests are run out of order or in parallel. Chaining into one scenario makes the
  #   dependency explicit and safe - Sections 1 and 2 deliberately share a herd.

  @staffdata @herds:5:admincheck
  Background:
    Given the staff user is logged in to the BISS internal portal as "agr4442"

  @e2e @admin-check @appeal @history
  Scenario: Staff runs an admin check through approval, then rejection and appeal

    # SECTION 1 - AT-TC-01 (BISSAGL-14850)
    # Validates: starting a check applies the in-progress STOP and records it verbatim.
    When the staff user opens the Active Farmer screen for the next admin-check herd for scheme year "2024"
    And the staff user starts the active farmer admin check
    Then the application history should record "Active Farmer Admin Check in Progress Stop has been Applied with comment: Admin check started manually"

    # SECTION 2 - AT-TC-02 (BISSAGL-14842)
    # Validates: approving the check LIFTS the stop and carries the staff comment into the
    # note. Runs against the same herd as Section 1 - see the ordering note above.
    When the staff user returns to the Active Farmer screen for the same admin-check herd for scheme year "2024"
    And the staff user completes the admin check with the following result
      | result | APPROVED  |
      | notes  | Test Note |
    Then the application history should record "Active Farmer Admin Check in Progress Stop has been Lifted with comment: Test Note"

    # SECTION 3 - AT-TC-03 (BISSAGL-14840)
    # Validates: the full appeal path on a fresh herd - reject, appeal with evidence, then
    # approve the appeal, which lifts the stop and records the appeal comment.
    When the staff user opens the Active Farmer screen for the next admin-check herd for scheme year "2024"
    And the staff user starts the active farmer admin check
    And the staff user completes the admin check with the following result
      | result | REJECTED  |
      | notes  | Test Note |
    And the staff user raises an appeal with supporting evidence
    And the staff user completes the admin check with the following result
      | result | APPROVED        |
      | notes  | Appeal Approved |
    Then the application history should record "Active Farmer Admin Check in Progress Stop has been Lifted with comment: Appeal Approved"
